        "description": {
            "value": "<p><strong>Once Per Turn</strong>\u00a0- Self - 3/Long Rest - Magical</p><p>Before you roll [[/r 1d6]] to determine if your spell will be a @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-class-features.Item.yXSOvWE0v2BWMshU]{random wild surge}, you can force your spell to be a @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.JournalEntry.FEMWrKEyIrd0s6BT.JournalEntryPage.VJrA212Hv3sI9yQv]{wild surge}. You still roll the 1d6. If you roll a 5 or 6, your surge's effect is rolled on the table one level higher (which is the standard rule for triggering a surge in two different ways). For example, if you voluntarily surge on a 2nd level spell and then roll a 6 for a random surge, you roll your surge on the 3rd level wild surge table.</p><p>\u200b\u200b\u200b\u200b</p>",
